## 🧪 2. Comprehensive Test Cases

### Scenario A: Frictionless Browsing & Cart
| Test ID | Action | Expected Result | Pass/Fail |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **A1** | Load homepage as a guest. | Animations load smoothly. Navbar/Footer are visible. No login prompts appear. | |
| **A2** | Click on a category filter (e.g., "Spices"). | Only products matching "Spices" are displayed. | |
| **A3** | Click a product card. | Routes to Product Detail Page. Navbar/Footer disappear. | |
| **A4** | Change product size variant (e.g., 50g to 100g). | Price dynamically updates. URL remains stable. | |

### Scenario B: The Unified Authentication Gateway
| Test ID | Action | Expected Result | Pass/Fail |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **B1** | Click "BUY IT NOW" as a guest. | Redirects instantly to the Auth Portal ([EntryAuthPage](file:///c:/e%20com%20c/client/src/pages/EntryAuthPage.jsx#9-377)). | |
| **B2** | Register new account with invalid email. | System rejects request. OTP is not sent. | |
| **B3** | Complete Registration + OTP successfully. | Logs user in and *automatically redirects* them back to the Checkout page for the item they clicked. | |
| **B4** | Click "BUY IT NOW" while already logged in. | Bypasses Auth completely and goes straight to Checkout. | |

### Scenario C: Checkout & Coupon Engine
| Test ID | Action | Expected Result | Pass/Fail |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **C1** | Progress to Step 2 of Checkout. | Only "Cash on Delivery" is visible. Card/UPI options are entirely hidden. | |
| **C2** | Apply an expired or invalid coupon code. | Red error message indicating invalidity. Total remains unchanged. | |
| **C3** | Apply a valid active coupon code. | Green success badge appears "Code Applied". Total mathematically reduces correctly. | |
| **C4** | Place Order. | Redirects to Success Screen. Order is written to MongoDB. | |

### Scenario D: Email Notification Pipeline
| Test ID | Action | Expected Result | Pass/Fail |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **D1** | Check customer email after placing order. | Receives styled HTML email with Venthulir logo and correct line items. | |
| **D2** | Check `theoptime.io@gmail.com` inbox. | Receives identical "NEW ORDER RECEIVED" ping instantly. | |
| **D3** | Verify coupon display in email. | If a coupon was used, the email explicitly shows the "Discount" line item and subtraction. | |

### Scenario E: Real-Time Admin Dashboard
| Test ID | Action | Expected Result | Pass/Fail |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **E1** | Login as standard user and attempt to hit `/admin`. | Forced redirect back to home page. Access Denied. | |
| **E2** | Login specifically as `shreenithya111@gmail.com`. | Grants access to the Admin Panel. | |
| **E3** | Have the Admin Panel open on "Orders" while a separate incognito window places a new order. | Within 5 seconds, the new order popups into the Admin list without a manual page refresh. | |
| **E4** | Inspect Order Details in Admin Panel. | Admin can see the Phone Number, full Street Address Breakdown, and the explicit Coupon deduction calculation. | |
| **E5** | Generate a new Coupon in the Coupons tab. | Coupon immediately appears in the Active list and is usable on the frontend checkout. | |

### Scenario F: Inventory Control & Product Management (Admin)
| Test ID | Action | Expected Result | Pass/Fail |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **F1** | Add a new product via "Add Harvest". | Product receives a unique **VNT-XXXXXX** SKU. `currentStock` matches `initialStock`. | |
| **F2** | Edit an existing product's price or description. | Changes reflect instantly in the ShopGrid. Variants and badges remain stable. | |
| **F3** | Restock a product via the Inventory tab. | `currentStock` increases. "OUT OF STOCK" badge is removed if stock was zero. | |
| **F4** | Place a "Buy It Now" order for a low-stock item. | Stock reduces atomically. If it reaches 0, the product shows "Out of Stock" to other users. | |
| **F5** | Delete a product from the Admin dashboard. | Product is immediately removed from the customer ShopGrid and category filters. | |

### Scenario G: Advanced Security & Guest Support
| Test ID | Action | Expected Result | Pass/Fail |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **G1** | Trigger "Forgot Password" for a registered email. | Receives a Reset OTP valid for **30 seconds**. Invalid/Expired OTPs are rejected. | |
| **G2** | Complete Reset Password + Login with new credentials. | Session is established. Old password no longer grants access. | |
| **G3** | Submit a message via "Contact Us" as a guest. | Success toast appears. Message is saved to the backend with timestamp. | |
| **G4** | Admin resolves a support message. | Message is marked as "Resolved" in Admin list; no longer appears in "Pending". | |
| **G5** | Update User Profile (Name/Phone) in Settings. | Database persistence is verified. New name appears in Header greeting. | |

### Scenario H: Admin Shipping Charge & Customer Order Cancellation
| Test ID | Action | Expected Result | Pass/Fail |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **H1** | Admin sets a non-zero Shipping Charge on a product. | Shipping charge natively saves to MongoDB and persists across edits. | |
| **H2** | Customer initiates checkout for that item. | The explicit Admin-defined Shipping charge is retrieved, displayed, and mathematically added to the Subtotal. | |
| **H3** | Order attempt fails due to 0 exact stock. | The UI catches the backend 400 error and surfaces an inline, elegantly-styled red warning banner (no alert popups). | |
| **H4** | Customer views "Your Orders" in their Dashboard. | The real-time MongoDB database connection arrays the active order at the top, showing as "Pending". | |
| **H5** | Customer clicks "Cancel Order" on a Pending order. | The order status switches to "Cancelled". Most importantly, the `inventoryController` natively restores the stock. | |
| **H6** | Admin dynamically updates order status to "Shipped". | The responsive tracking graphic in the Customer Dashboard instantly jumps forward. | |

